# 🔹 Longest Common Subsequence (LCS)

Given two strings,

Find the **longest subsequence** common to both.

---

Example

```text
String1

ABCBDAB

String2

BDCABA
```

LCS:

```text
BCBA
```

Length:

```text
4
```

---

### DP Recurrence

If characters match:

[
dp[i][j]=1+dp[i-1][j-1]
]

Otherwise:

[
dp[i][j]=
\max(dp[i-1][j],dp[i][j-1])
]

---

### Complexity

Time:

[
O(nm)
]

Space:

[
O(nm)
]

---

# 🔹 0/1 Knapsack

Given:

* Weight
* Value
* Capacity

Each item can be chosen:

* Once
* Or not at all

(No fractions allowed)

---

Example

| Item | Weight | Value |
| ---- | ------ | ----- |
| A    | 2      | 3     |
| B    | 3      | 4     |
| C    | 4      | 5     |
| D    | 5      | 6     |

Capacity:

```text
5
```

Optimal:

Choose:

A + B

Total Value:

```text
7
```

---

### DP Recurrence

If:

[
weight_i\le W
]

Then

[
dp[i][W]
========

\max
(
dp[i-1][W],
value_i+dp[i-1][W-weight_i]
)
]

Else

[
dp[i][W]
========

dp[i-1][W]
]

---

### Complexity

Time:

[
O(nW)
]

Space:

[
O(nW)
]

