# 🔹 Greedy vs Dynamic Programming

| Feature            | Greedy     | Dynamic Programming |
| ------------------ | ---------- | ------------------- |
| Local Choice       | Yes        | No                  |
| Revisits Decisions | No         | Yes                 |
| Stores Results     | No         | Yes                 |
| Always Optimal     | Not always | Yes (if DP applies) |

---

# 🔹 Common GATE Traps

### Trap 1

0/1 Knapsack

❌ Not Greedy

✅ Dynamic Programming

---

### Trap 2

Memoization uses recursion.

Tabulation uses iteration.

---

### Trap 3

LCS is about **subsequence**, **not substring**.

A subsequence need **not** be contiguous.

---

### Trap 4

DP is useful only if there are **overlapping subproblems**.

